// cities.js
// Turns a birth city + country into coordinates without calling any
// external service. Two layers:
//
//   1. cities-data.js — the full worldwide dataset (~31,000 cities).
//      Generated by running build-cities.mjs (Cloudflare's build step).
//      If it hasn't run yet, this layer is simply empty and layer 2 is used.
//
//   2. A built-in list of major world cities, so the site works even
//      before the full dataset is generated.
//
// If neither layer matches, we fall back to New York — which is
// exactly what the old code did when a city couldn't be resolved.

